    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small sliding beads that were used to suspend the inro, tobacco pouches and money purses from the wearer's belt. These beads were made out of a variety of materials such as glass, bone, wood, lacquer, jade and ivory. They sometimes featured intricate carved designs or were carved into the shape of animals or human figures.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
